description:
The AstigVegan book, “Filipino Vegan” is finally here!

“Filipino Vegan” features both improved and new, never-before-released recipes as well as personal stories and insights to hopefully inspire those looking to learn more about the vegan way of living. Although the concept seems ambitious, Anvil Publishing, National Bookstore, and RG Enriquez-Diez worked hard to ensure the recipes are approachable, beginner-friendly, and simple. Not to mention the book is affordable, too, so all walks of life can have access to it. 

“Filipino Vegan” will launch at the Manila International Book Fair at the SMX Convention Center on September 18, Sunday, at 11:15am.

To register and get a free pass: 

https://app.eventplus.io/manilainternational-bookfair

📌 Registration is until September 14 only.
📌 The entrance pass is valid for one day only.
